fields.description:
Im getting various warnings on a pretty out of the box alloy project. I dont know where these warnings are coming from, but they dont look good and they indicate a problem.

{noformat}
[WARN]  [Hyperloop] couldn't find class Protocol * {"name":"protocol","optional":false,"type":{"type":"objc_pointer","value":"Protocol *"}}
[WARN]  [Hyperloop] Not sure how to handle: name= nodeInteraction type= unknown type: 119 value= unknown type: 119
[WARN]  [Hyperloop] Not sure how to handle: name= eventValues type= unknown type: 119 value= unknown type: 119
[WARN]  [Hyperloop] Not sure how to handle: name= __fpu_fcw type= unknown type: 119 value= unknown type: 119
[WARN]  [Hyperloop] Not sure how to handle: name= __fpu_fsw type= unknown type: 119 value= unknown type: 119
[WARN]  [Hyperloop] Not sure how to handle: name= __fpu_stmm0 type= unknown type: 119 value= unknown type: 119
[WARN]  [Hyperloop] Not sure how to handle: name= __fpu_stmm1 type= unknown type: 119 value= unknown type: 119
[WARN]  [Hyperloop] Not sure how to handle: name= __fpu_stmm2 type= unknown type: 119 value= unknown type: 11
{noformat}
There are many lines after, with quite the same syntax. See pastebin: https://pastebin.com/8XAk4dcu
fields.environment: Tested on iOS Simulator, Ti SDK 6.2.2.GA, Hyperloop 2.1.3

comments.body: Hello, Try updating Hyperloop to latest version.

[~uzbbert],

I just wanted to follow up here. Did you manage to follow the instructions provided earlier? Let us know if you still experience any issue. We would be happy to assist you.
Best Regards!
Hi, this has likely been an old hyperloop issue which is now fixed. I havent encountered it anymore.
